category comment: 

clue: The New Testament's I Timothy says, "Drink no longer water, but use a little" of this "for thy stomach's sake"

response: wine

clue: Cole Porter wrote, "I get no kick from" this, "mere alcohol doesn't thrill me at all"

response: champagne

clue: This cocktail may be dry, like the wit of H.L. Mencken, said to have called it "the only American invention as perfect as the sonnet"

response: a martini

clue: In "Anna Christie" Greta Garbo requested this, "ginger ale on the side. And don't be stingy, baby"

response: whiskey

clue: It's the line in "Treasure Island" that precedes & follows "drink and the devil had done for the rest"

response: yo-ho-ho and a bottle of rum

